1
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:23,149
There's nothing we can do, bro.

2
00:00:23,232 --> 00:00:24,942
<i>The good news is</i>
<i>they didn't get the money.</i>

3
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:25,985
<i>I'm sorry, Gem.</i>

4
00:00:26,068 --> 00:00:27,611
You did everything you could.

5
00:00:27,695 --> 00:00:30,197
- I'll get you out of there.
- <i>Teo, don't.</i>

6
00:00:30,281 --> 00:00:31,407
<i>You and your father are in danger.</i>

7
00:00:31,490 --> 00:00:32,783
I saw it earlier.

8
00:00:32,867 --> 00:00:34,869
There are still people watching our house.

9
00:00:34,952 --> 00:00:35,911
<i>I thought it was already over.</i>

10
00:00:35,995 --> 00:00:36,954
<i>Thank you for everything.</i>

11
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:38,956
<i>For taking care of Ace, and most of all,</i>

12
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:39,915
<i>for putting up with me.</i>

13
00:00:39,999 --> 00:00:42,293
<i>If I were you,</i>
<i>I'd have left long ago.</i>

14
00:00:42,376 --> 00:00:43,919
<i>Actually, Mama,</i>
<i>I want to go somewhere.</i>

15
00:00:44,003 --> 00:00:45,212
What are you telling me?

16
00:00:45,296 --> 00:00:46,297
<i>Leon is in the Philippines.</i>

17
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:47,840
He's looking for the money you took.

18
00:00:47,923 --> 00:00:49,341
- No way.
- Let's pay him.

19
00:00:49,425 --> 00:00:50,551
<i>So you can have peace.</i>

20
00:00:50,634 --> 00:00:52,011
There's trouble here!

21
00:00:52,094 --> 00:00:53,429
<i>Sir Ace came!</i>

22
00:00:53,512 --> 00:00:56,223
<i>He's going to kill Ma'am Gem and Teo!</i>

23
00:00:58,684 --> 00:00:59,685
That's enough!

24
00:00:59,769 --> 00:01:00,770
Pick him up!

25
00:01:02,563 --> 00:01:05,691
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

26
00:01:34,428 --> 00:01:36,096
Hello?

27
00:01:36,847 --> 00:01:40,643
Is this the nearest
police station in Villa Pacifico?

28
00:01:44,647 --> 00:01:46,941
Ace, stop it! Let's end this!

29
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,450
You see this?

30
00:01:56,534 --> 00:01:58,118
This will be your grave.

31
00:01:58,202 --> 00:02:00,329
-
Ace!

32
00:02:01,872 --> 00:02:04,625
- Ace, I'm begging you, stop!

33
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:06,043
Ace!

34
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:09,463


35
00:02:10,381 --> 00:02:11,298
Gem.

36
00:02:13,217 --> 00:02:14,802
Ace, stop.

37
00:02:14,885 --> 00:02:16,095
Don't you want this to end?

38
00:02:16,178 --> 00:02:17,429
So we can finally find out

39
00:02:17,513 --> 00:02:19,974
who your lover is, who the traitor is,

40
00:02:20,057 --> 00:02:21,767
and who's telling the truth?

41
00:02:21,851 --> 00:02:24,478
-
Hey!

42
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:28,315


43
00:02:28,399 --> 00:02:30,067
You bastard.

44
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,735
What were you doing there?

45
00:02:31,819 --> 00:02:33,696
At the money exchange
during the kidnapping?

46
00:02:33,779 --> 00:02:35,072
What business did you have there?

47
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:37,032
What were you looking for?
Tell me!

48
00:02:40,077 --> 00:02:40,911


49
00:02:40,995 --> 00:02:42,454
And this driver.

50
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,665
The minute you were introduced,

51
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:46,250
you called her with a different name.

52
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,794
Is she the ex
you were talking about?

53
00:02:48,878 --> 00:02:50,296
Ace, that's not true.

54
00:02:50,921 --> 00:02:52,965
- It's nothing like that.
Are you Gem's lover?

55
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:55,384
Or are there two of you?

56
00:02:56,135 --> 00:02:56,969
Three?

57
00:02:57,052 --> 00:02:59,305
A group thing?

58
00:02:59,388 --> 00:03:02,349
- Please, stop!

59
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:03,350
Damn, Gem.

60
00:03:03,434 --> 00:03:05,561
You're losing your mind.
It's nothing like that!

61
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:06,770
Is that your kink?

62
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:08,355
Pretending it's a kidnapping

63
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:10,649
just to get money so you can escape?

64
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:12,568
I'm not leaving.

65
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:14,153
Tell me, Gem.

66
00:03:14,236 --> 00:03:16,196
Is that why you took
all your jewelry and hid it?

67
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:18,240
Because you were planning to leave,

68
00:03:18,324 --> 00:03:20,117
- to run away?
No!

69
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,201


70
00:03:21,285 --> 00:03:22,912
- Ace, don't!
Don't! Don't!

71
00:03:22,995 --> 00:03:24,830
- Don't!
Gem!

72
00:03:25,748 --> 00:03:27,833


73
00:03:27,917 --> 00:03:29,251


74
00:03:29,335 --> 00:03:31,253
Looks like we have a winner.

75
00:03:31,337 --> 00:03:33,047


76
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:38,344


77
00:03:43,682 --> 00:03:44,516
Yes, Pa?

78
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,601
What happened?

79
00:03:45,684 --> 00:03:47,561
Nothing's happening.
I'm good.

80
00:03:47,645 --> 00:03:49,605
Don't do anything stupid, okay?

81
00:03:49,688 --> 00:03:52,358
Getting our money back
from the kidnappers is stupid?

82
00:03:52,441 --> 00:03:53,609
What?

83
00:03:53,692 --> 00:03:54,944
I've found the kidnappers.

84
00:03:55,027 --> 00:03:56,278
<i>Gem has two accomplices.</i>

85
00:03:56,362 --> 00:03:58,572
One of them is her lover, I'm sure of it.

86
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:01,075
I'm going to
turn this all around, and you'll see--

87
00:04:01,158 --> 00:04:01,992
No!

88
00:04:02,076 --> 00:04:03,661
<i>I'm telling you now,</i>

89
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:05,287
stop this nonsense, okay?

90
00:04:05,371 --> 00:04:06,872
<i>And I'm telling you right now!</i>

91
00:04:06,956 --> 00:04:09,583
Don't do anything unless I say so!

92
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:12,670
You're not here,
so I'll do whatever I want.

93
00:04:13,295 --> 00:04:14,129
Ace!

94
00:04:15,214 --> 00:04:16,173
Ace!

95
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:19,885
Where were we?

96
00:04:22,221 --> 00:04:24,223


97
00:04:26,517 --> 00:04:28,143
Who is your man, Gem?

98
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:31,063
My bet goes to Teo.

99
00:04:31,146 --> 00:04:32,982
Ace, don't!

100
00:04:33,065 --> 00:04:34,483
- Ace!
Drop it!

101
00:04:35,401 --> 00:04:36,944
- Ace!
Drop the gun!

102
00:04:37,027 --> 00:04:38,988
Oh, my goodness, Ace!

103
00:04:39,071 --> 00:04:41,573
Teo, how could you?

104
00:04:42,241 --> 00:04:44,702
We accepted you,
and this is how you repay us?

105
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:46,453
Ma'am, I was just defending myself!

106
00:04:46,537 --> 00:04:49,540
Sir Ace shot that man,
I just tried to stop him!

107
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:50,958
He was going to shoot us too!

108
00:04:51,834 --> 00:04:53,711
He's telling the truth, Mama.

109
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:55,087
You lying piece of shit!

110
00:04:55,838 --> 00:04:58,215
One of them is the kidnapper
and Gem's lover!

111
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:01,552


112
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:06,265
Lower your guns!

113
00:05:06,348 --> 00:05:07,725
Sir, it's this guy!

114
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:10,561
Arrest him. He's the one responsible!

115
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:12,896
No, sir! That's not true!

116
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:14,982
Ace beat that man up and even shot him!

117
00:05:15,065 --> 00:05:16,442
He was going to shoot us too!

118
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:18,110
Look, we're in a pit, sir!

119
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:19,778
Sir, everything he's saying is true.

120
00:05:19,862 --> 00:05:22,114
Ace was trying to kill us.
Please believe us!

121
00:05:22,197 --> 00:05:23,073
Sir!

122
00:05:23,157 --> 00:05:25,159
All of you, come with us to the station!

123
00:05:26,618 --> 00:05:28,162
Do you know who I am?

124
00:05:28,245 --> 00:05:29,663
I'm Judge Verona.

125
00:05:30,247 --> 00:05:31,457
Yes, Judge.

126
00:05:50,559 --> 00:05:51,810
Judge.

127
00:05:51,894 --> 00:05:53,729

You'll come with me to the station

128
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:55,856
once your condition stabilizes.

129
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:58,317
You'll admit
that everything is your fault.

130
00:05:59,234 --> 00:06:01,820
I've prepared an affidavit. Sign it.

131
00:06:01,904 --> 00:06:05,407
Judge, me, Ma'am Gem,
and the man Sir Ace shot,

132
00:06:05,491 --> 00:06:07,534
we're the ones who were almost killed.

133
00:06:07,618 --> 00:06:09,411
Shouldn't Sir Ace be the one you take?

134
00:06:09,495 --> 00:06:11,497
Your father needs money.

135
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:13,665
That's why you kidnapped my son.

136
00:06:13,749 --> 00:06:15,709
You and Gem are in a relationship.

137
00:06:15,793 --> 00:06:16,794
You're accomplices.

138
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:19,630
There's no proof of what you're saying.

139
00:06:21,090 --> 00:06:23,801
Why did you go to the farmhouse
when no one told you to?

140
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,552
Judge, someone called me.

141
00:06:27,346 --> 00:06:29,556
I didn't answer,
so they sent a text instead.

142
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:32,142
The place seemed familiar, so I went.

143
00:06:32,226 --> 00:06:34,937
You told me you spoke to that person.

144
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:36,730
Was it a man or a woman?

145
00:06:36,814 --> 00:06:39,525
They called,
but I didn't actually talk to them.

146
00:06:41,527 --> 00:06:43,779
"Go to Villa Pacifico, now."

147
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:45,781
Give me the number.

148
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:53,956


149
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:57,501
I'll have it traced.

150
00:06:57,584 --> 00:07:01,213
If I find out you're lying
and that person is your accomplice,

151
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:02,840
you'll regret this.

152
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:06,510
Judge, I've already covered up
so much for you...

153
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:07,886
and for Sir Ace.

154
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:10,222
Did you just make a threat?

155
00:07:11,723 --> 00:07:13,016
What do you want?

156
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,768
To get out of here.

157
00:07:15,394 --> 00:07:18,147
To stay alive
because I still have a family to support.

158
00:07:18,814 --> 00:07:20,899
If I hadn't taken the gun from your son,

159
00:07:20,983 --> 00:07:22,359
I'd be the one dead.

160
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,778
It's your word against ours.

161
00:07:24,862 --> 00:07:28,115
And our word is more powerful than yours.

162
00:07:28,198 --> 00:07:30,159
And that only means one thing.

163
00:07:30,242 --> 00:07:32,286
You're not leaving this place.

164
00:07:34,496 --> 00:07:36,331
Keep a close watch on him.

165
00:07:46,216 --> 00:07:47,634
Ma'am, Patient Crisanto.

166
00:07:47,718 --> 00:07:49,011
All right. He's here for an X-ray.

167
00:07:49,094 --> 00:07:50,262
Come in.

168
00:08:04,568 --> 00:08:06,069
Just wait a moment.

169
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:26,006
Where's the patient?

170
00:08:26,465 --> 00:08:28,550
- Wasn't he with you?
- He's not there.

171
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:53,450
If you had just followed my orders,

172
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,494
Teo wouldn't have escaped!

173
00:08:56,328 --> 00:08:59,706
Do everything you can
to find Mateo Crisanto!

174
00:09:04,711 --> 00:09:05,963
Where is your secretary?

175
00:09:06,964 --> 00:09:08,507
She's just around there. Where else?

176
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,259
Ma'am, about that--

177
00:09:10,342 --> 00:09:11,843
Where's Teo?

178
00:09:12,761 --> 00:09:15,389
- What?
- I don't have time for games.

179
00:09:15,472 --> 00:09:17,224
Where is he?

180
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,142
Isn't he detained at the hospital?

181
00:09:19,226 --> 00:09:20,310
Wrong!

182
00:09:20,394 --> 00:09:21,687
He escaped.

183
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:25,232
And now I want to hear
from his girlfriend where he is.

184
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:27,359
N-No, I don't really know.

185
00:09:27,442 --> 00:09:28,986
I don't--

186
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:31,071
Now stop acting like a bumbling idiot!

187
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:32,614
Answer the question.

188
00:09:32,698 --> 00:09:35,534
- I don't know.
- What's the matter, Larajean?

189
00:09:35,617 --> 00:09:37,202
Don't you even know what happened?

190
00:09:37,286 --> 00:09:39,371
All I know is what you told me earlier

191
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:43,000
about Sir Ace and Ma'am Gem,
and that Teo was accused too.

192
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,793
- That's all!
- Liar!

193
00:09:44,876 --> 00:09:46,295
Give me your phone!

194
00:09:46,378 --> 00:09:48,755
Judge, that's not right.
That's an invasion of privacy--

195
00:09:48,839 --> 00:09:50,340
Shut up! Give me your phone!

196
00:09:58,557 --> 00:10:02,269
No calls, no texts from Teo? Nothing?

197
00:10:03,812 --> 00:10:05,522
You and Teo aren't in a relationship.

198
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:10,193
You just pretended to be,
to cover up his relationship with Gem.

199
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:25,208
Sir Alonzo, where are you going?

200
00:10:25,751 --> 00:10:29,755
Sir, I left some tools at home.

201
00:10:29,838 --> 00:10:30,839
I'll just get them.

202
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:33,175
No need.
We have a complete set of tools here.

203
00:10:33,258 --> 00:10:35,218
And the job I gave you
isn't that hard, is it?

204
00:10:36,261 --> 00:10:37,387
Sir.

205
00:10:38,388 --> 00:10:39,431
What is this about?

206
00:10:39,514 --> 00:10:41,183
Oh, it's from the judge.

207
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:43,602
Wait for him.
He said he has something to tell you.

208
00:10:44,603 --> 00:10:46,730
- Let me just call my son--
- No need.

209
00:10:47,606 --> 00:10:49,316
- Sir?
- There's a problem with Teo.

210
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:51,443
You can't leave until we find him.

211
00:10:52,235 --> 00:10:53,904
Go ahead, head inside first.

212
00:10:54,696 --> 00:10:56,031
Just relax there.

213
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:57,366
Go on.

214
00:11:29,773 --> 00:11:30,941
Boss.

215
00:11:32,317 --> 00:11:33,276
This is Yana.

216
00:11:34,528 --> 00:11:35,987
<i>Gimo and I are in trouble.</i>

217
00:11:37,823 --> 00:11:39,074
We got caught.

218
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,912
We tried to escape,
but the Veronas cornered us.

219
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:48,917
Boss.

220
00:11:54,965 --> 00:11:55,966
Boss!

221
00:11:56,842 --> 00:11:59,177
We're at the hospital right now.

222
00:11:59,636 --> 00:12:03,014
<i>Gimo's in a coma. He might not make it.</i>

223
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:05,642
Boss, please help us.

224
00:12:07,227 --> 00:12:08,270
<i>Boss!</i>

225
00:12:09,938 --> 00:12:11,189
Boss!

226
00:12:11,273 --> 00:12:13,567
Stay put. Help is coming.

227
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:17,195
Just don't do anything
that will make the Veronas suspicious.

228
00:12:17,612 --> 00:12:19,698
Get us out of here.

229
00:12:35,172 --> 00:12:37,674
Teo.

230
00:13:01,656 --> 00:13:03,658
Good morning, Gem.
How are you feeling?

231
00:13:04,493 --> 00:13:05,911
Tired.

232
00:13:05,994 --> 00:13:07,120
Understandable.

233
00:13:07,204 --> 00:13:09,414
You suffered a few superficial scratches

234
00:13:09,498 --> 00:13:11,416
and some minor bruising.

235
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:12,626
Nothing serious.

236
00:13:12,709 --> 00:13:15,837
Likely from recent strain or impact.

237
00:13:15,921 --> 00:13:16,922
We've cleaned them,

238
00:13:17,005 --> 00:13:20,967
and there are no signs
of infection or internal injury.

239
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:25,722
You're also experiencing fatigue,
dizziness, and nausea.

240
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:29,184
But these are normal,
especially in this condition.

241
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,021
What condition?

242
00:13:33,104 --> 00:13:35,524
Congratulations! You're pregnant!

243
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:45,408
Thank you, Doctor.

244
00:14:01,174 --> 00:14:02,801
Who's the father?

245
00:14:03,426 --> 00:14:05,428
It's definitely not Ace.

246
00:14:05,512 --> 00:14:07,514
What makes you say it's not Ace's?

247
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:11,726
We have been waiting a long time
for you to have a baby.

248
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:13,937
But you haven't had any children.

249
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,565
And then all of a sudden, you're pregnant!

250
00:14:16,648 --> 00:14:19,943
Now that Ace knows
you're having an affair,

251
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:21,486
that man's probably the father.

252
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:23,613
We need a paternity test.

253
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:25,115
Is that even possible?

254
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:26,658
Yes, it is.

255
00:14:26,741 --> 00:14:30,328
You can do it as early
as eight weeks into the pregnancy.

256
00:14:30,412 --> 00:14:32,122
I can talk to the doctor.

257
00:14:32,205 --> 00:14:33,415
Then do it.

258
00:14:34,749 --> 00:14:36,668
Gem, tell me the truth.

259
00:14:36,751 --> 00:14:37,836
Is the baby mine?

260
00:14:41,798 --> 00:14:43,300
Even if I answer you...

261
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:46,052
...you won't believe me either way.

262
00:14:47,137 --> 00:14:51,349
Do you know that
that answer makes you look guilty?

263
00:14:51,433 --> 00:14:53,977
Just answer
with a simple yes or no.

264
00:14:54,686 --> 00:14:57,314
Well, whose do you think it is?

265
00:14:58,356 --> 00:15:00,191
Oh, my goodness!

266
00:15:00,734 --> 00:15:03,236
This is going to be a major disaster!

267
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:07,574
No one can know that you're pregnant, Gem!

268
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:10,535
Especially if that baby is not Ace's!

269
00:15:11,036 --> 00:15:12,996
It's going to be a big scandal!

270
00:15:13,079 --> 00:15:15,749
You need to stay quiet, Gem.

271
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:17,959
For your baby's sake.

272
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:20,629
Whether it's Ace's or not.

273
00:15:31,723 --> 00:15:33,224
Teo.

274
00:15:33,308 --> 00:15:37,187
I've been messaging
and calling you for a while now!

275
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,648
<i>Madam and the judge</i>
<i>have been asking me where you are!</i>

276
00:15:39,731 --> 00:15:41,733
The judge was absolutely furious
when we spoke.

277
00:15:41,816 --> 00:15:44,027
They don't believe we're together.

278
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:45,987
Are the rumors I'm hearing true?

279
00:15:46,071 --> 00:15:47,530
Does the truth even matter anymore?

280
00:15:47,614 --> 00:15:50,408
People choose
what they want to believe in now.

281
00:15:50,492 --> 00:15:51,409
You included.

282
00:15:51,493 --> 00:15:53,078
Where are you?

283
00:15:53,912 --> 00:15:56,289
Just nearby. Safe.

284
00:15:56,873 --> 00:15:58,500
<i>I have a favor.</i>

285
00:15:58,583 --> 00:15:59,834
<i>I can't pick Issay up...</i>

286
00:15:59,918 --> 00:16:02,587
She's at a seminar in Tagaytay.
Could you pick her up for me?

287
00:16:03,588 --> 00:16:04,923
Tagaytay?

288
00:16:05,006 --> 00:16:06,800
I know, it's far.

289
00:16:07,258 --> 00:16:08,343
Could you pick her up for me?

290
00:16:08,927 --> 00:16:12,430
Tell her not to go home
and not to post anything online.

291
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:15,892
Fine. All right.

292
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,686
<i>Be careful, Teo.</i>

293
00:16:17,769 --> 00:16:20,814
I know you couldn't have done
what they're saying.

294
00:16:20,897 --> 00:16:21,898
Thank you.

295
00:16:26,403 --> 00:16:28,822
Ouch!

296
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:41,918
What's going on?

297
00:16:43,628 --> 00:16:45,755
I did what you wanted.

298
00:16:47,799 --> 00:16:49,384
I kept my mouth shut.

299
00:16:49,884 --> 00:16:50,719
Well...

300
00:16:51,136 --> 00:16:55,140
we wanted to make sure
you wouldn't try anything foolish.

301
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:05,150
You can't do this to me.

302
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:07,819
Open the door!

303
00:17:07,902 --> 00:17:09,863
Let me out of here!

304
00:17:11,906 --> 00:17:14,701
Ace, please... let me out...

305
00:17:14,784 --> 00:17:15,618
Gem, enough!

306
00:17:15,702 --> 00:17:17,662
There's nothing you can do.

307
00:17:17,746 --> 00:17:19,080
Do you think we can trust you again?

308
00:17:19,164 --> 00:17:21,291
You won't leave this room unless I say so.

309
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,251
Let me go.

310
00:17:28,965 --> 00:17:30,717
Mama...

311
00:17:46,775 --> 00:17:48,902
This is enough! Ace!

312
00:17:48,985 --> 00:17:50,069
Ace!

313
00:17:50,737 --> 00:17:52,947
Let me out! Please!

314
00:18:06,711 --> 00:18:07,712
Ace!

315
00:18:10,256 --> 00:18:11,591
Mama!

316
00:18:11,674 --> 00:18:15,345
Ace, please! Let me out!

317
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:18,890
I'll keep my mouth shut!

318
00:18:28,316 --> 00:18:30,693
- Have you seen my father?
- <i>No.</i>

319
00:18:30,777 --> 00:18:32,570
I called him earlier,
but he didn't pick up.

320
00:18:32,654 --> 00:18:35,532
<i>I stopped by the car wash. It was closed.</i>

321
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:37,200
Wait a minute, Teo.

322
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:41,204
What's going on?

323
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:42,872
<i>Raya messaged me.</i>

324
00:18:42,956 --> 00:18:45,750
She said that you're the prime suspect
in what happened at the Verona farm.

325
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:49,671
Yes, they're forcing me to take the fall
for Ace because he shot someone.

326
00:18:49,754 --> 00:18:51,548
I just need to hide for now, Ronnie.

327
00:18:52,006 --> 00:18:53,341
What can I do to help?

328
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:55,176
<i>Do you need a lawyer?</i>

329
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:57,428
Yes, I'm going to need one.

330
00:18:57,512 --> 00:18:59,514
<i>I'm just sorting something out for now.</i>

331
00:18:59,597 --> 00:19:01,224
Don't head back to the house just yet.

332
00:19:01,933 --> 00:19:03,309
But maybe...

333
00:19:03,393 --> 00:19:04,644
you can just watch it from afar.

334
00:19:05,562 --> 00:19:06,688
Okay, Teo.

335
00:19:06,771 --> 00:19:08,940
I'll also text you where I am right now.

336
00:19:09,023 --> 00:19:11,025
Come see me after work, okay?

337
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:13,570
No problem.

338
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:16,155
What about... Uncle Alonzo?
What are we going to do?

339
00:19:16,239 --> 00:19:18,491
- And Issay?
- She's with Larajean.

340
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:21,369
I don't know where Papa is.

341
00:19:23,580 --> 00:19:26,749
Judge. You can't keep me here.

342
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:30,295
My family, friends, and Teo
will be looking for me.

343
00:19:30,378 --> 00:19:32,297
That's what I want to happen.

344
00:19:33,089 --> 00:19:35,049
I want your son to come get you!

345
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:37,427
What exactly did he do?

346
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:39,304
He kidnapped Ace.

347
00:19:39,387 --> 00:19:40,972
He was working with Gem!

348
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:43,349
Did you know
that they're having an affair?

349
00:19:43,433 --> 00:19:45,727
Judge, seriously--

350
00:19:46,227 --> 00:19:47,687
J-Judge!

351
00:19:48,396 --> 00:19:50,023
That's a serious accusation!

352
00:19:50,106 --> 00:19:51,524
My son wouldn't do that!

353
00:19:51,608 --> 00:19:53,318
Your son is a criminal, Alonzo.

354
00:19:53,401 --> 00:19:54,986
My son is not a criminal!

355
00:19:55,069 --> 00:19:56,988
I'd even bet my other leg on it!

356
00:19:57,864 --> 00:20:01,075
He would never scam, steal,
or kill anyone!

357
00:20:01,159 --> 00:20:02,952
Don't test my limits, Alonzo!

358
00:20:03,036 --> 00:20:03,870
Judge.

359
00:20:03,953 --> 00:20:05,038
Tell your son to come here!

360
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:06,164
Judge...

361
00:20:09,542 --> 00:20:11,294
Judge... it's Teo.

362
00:20:12,962 --> 00:20:13,838
Video.

363
00:20:14,672 --> 00:20:16,382
<i>Pa, why are you only answering now?</i>

364
00:20:16,466 --> 00:20:17,592
What's going on?

365
00:20:18,468 --> 00:20:19,886
I'm here at the judge's place.

366
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:23,306
<i>Isn't it obvious, Mateo? Hurry up!</i>

367
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:25,975
Don't you dare hurt my father!

368
00:20:28,269 --> 00:20:29,270
Teo.

369
00:20:29,771 --> 00:20:31,856
We need to tell someone else about this.

370
00:20:32,565 --> 00:20:35,234
So if anything happens to Papa,
you'll know who the suspects are.

371
00:20:35,318 --> 00:20:38,071
Someone with motive...
we need to tell the police.

372
00:20:56,714 --> 00:20:57,840
Do you have any knowledge...

373
00:20:57,924 --> 00:20:59,550
...of where Teo is hiding?

374
00:21:04,389 --> 00:21:05,974
Can you please let me out?

375
00:21:07,475 --> 00:21:09,143
I want to talk to my family.

376
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:14,357
Chief Del Mundo.

377
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:17,694
Mateo has filed a complaint against you.

378
00:21:17,777 --> 00:21:19,696
And what kind of complaint is that?

379
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:22,657
He denied all the complaints
you filed against him.

380
00:21:22,740 --> 00:21:24,617
And he also...

381
00:21:24,701 --> 00:21:27,453
filed a complaint against your son.

382
00:21:28,037 --> 00:21:31,624
I can squash those complaints
with the back of my hand.

383
00:21:32,917 --> 00:21:35,086
But thank you for telling me about it.

384
00:21:37,922 --> 00:21:39,257
Goodbye, Chief.

385
00:21:41,968 --> 00:21:43,011
Where is he?

386
00:21:44,345 --> 00:21:45,888
Judge.

387
00:21:45,972 --> 00:21:47,724
<i>Judge, please let me go!</i>

388
00:21:47,807 --> 00:21:49,434
<i>I'll talk to Teo!</i>

389
00:21:49,517 --> 00:21:51,811
<i>I'll make sure</i>
<i>he won't bother you anymore!</i>

390
00:21:51,894 --> 00:21:53,730
<i>- Judge!</i>
- That's Teo's father.

391
00:21:57,233 --> 00:21:58,985
Why are you dragging
other people into this?

392
00:21:59,068 --> 00:22:01,070
Because no one wants to tell us the truth.

393
00:22:01,154 --> 00:22:02,655
Because even if we do tell you...

394
00:22:02,739 --> 00:22:04,073
...you still won't believe it.

395
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:09,412
Is there anything real in this family?

396
00:22:11,164 --> 00:22:13,499
What about the human trafficking
allegations against you?

397
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:17,462
You're part of this family, Gem.

398
00:22:18,713 --> 00:22:22,300
And you know
what's important in this family.

399
00:22:22,383 --> 00:22:23,968
It's loyalty.

400
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:27,305
We don't tolerate traitors.

401
00:22:45,948 --> 00:22:48,326
<i>Earlier this morning, Mateo Crisanto filed</i>

402
00:22:48,409 --> 00:22:52,455
<i>a frustrated murder complaint</i>
<i>against Attorney Ace Verona.</i>

403
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:55,416
<i>Please tell us</i>
<i>what happened at the farmhouse.</i>

404
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:58,044
<i>Is it true that Attorney Ace Verona</i>
<i>almost killed you?</i>

405
00:22:58,127 --> 00:22:58,961
<i>It's true.</i>

406
00:22:59,837 --> 00:23:01,839
<i>He nearly killed me and his wife.</i>

407
00:23:01,923 --> 00:23:04,133
<i>As well as the man he's accusing</i>
<i>of being Ma'am Gem's lover.</i>

408
00:23:04,217 --> 00:23:06,094
<i>He even blamed me.</i>

409
00:23:06,177 --> 00:23:10,181
<i>I want to let everyone know</i>
<i>that Attorney Ace Verona nearly shot me.</i>

410
00:23:10,598 --> 00:23:13,142
<i>He also shot another man</i>
<i>who was with us that night.</i>

411
00:23:13,935 --> 00:23:15,436
<i>Tony Castellano.</i>

412
00:23:16,145 --> 00:23:19,190
<i>Even Ma'am Gem's life</i>
<i>is in danger in his hands.</i>

413
00:23:19,273 --> 00:23:21,776
<i>His father, Judge Verona,</i>
<i>also kidnapped my father.</i>

414
00:23:21,859 --> 00:23:23,820
<i>And they still have him.</i>

415
00:23:24,487 --> 00:23:26,489
My gosh, Divino! Look!

416
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:30,660
<i>Because of this,</i>
<i>I was detained in the hospital.</i>

417
00:23:30,743 --> 00:23:33,996
<i>But I had to escape</i>
<i>because I knew my life was in danger.</i>

418
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:39,252
<i>I had to bring these charges to light</i>
<i>to protect my life and my family's.</i>

419
00:23:39,335 --> 00:23:41,546
<i>We all know</i>
<i>what happened to Daniela Ordoñez</i>

420
00:23:41,629 --> 00:23:43,131
<i>when she went up against the Veronas.</i>

421
00:23:43,214 --> 00:23:46,467
<i>Daniela is dead,</i>
<i>and I refuse to end up like her.</i>

422
00:23:46,551 --> 00:23:48,136
<i>It can be recalled that the Veronas</i>

423
00:23:48,219 --> 00:23:49,887
<i>were also implicated in human trafficking</i>

424
00:23:49,971 --> 00:23:54,183
<i>and the death of supposed state witness,</i>
<i>Daniela Ordoñez.</i>

425
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:57,353
Is that all true, Ma?

426
00:23:58,312 --> 00:23:59,355
Ace!

427
00:23:59,438 --> 00:24:01,983
About that man, Teo, and Gem?

428
00:24:02,066 --> 00:24:03,192
Yes, Raya.

429
00:24:03,276 --> 00:24:06,112
- Gem cheated on your brother!
- And that automatically

430
00:24:06,195 --> 00:24:08,906
gives him the license
to do all those things?

431
00:24:10,032 --> 00:24:11,450
Well, I don't think so!

432
00:24:11,534 --> 00:24:12,827
I'm going to kill that Teo!

433
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:14,912
- Ace!
- Go to your room, Raya.

434
00:24:14,996 --> 00:24:16,998
What else
could you possibly hide from me, Pa?

435
00:24:17,999 --> 00:24:19,375
It's all over the news!

436
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:22,086
This is a conversation for adults.

437
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:23,880
Well, I am an adult, Pa!

438
00:24:23,963 --> 00:24:24,964
Raya.

439
00:24:25,590 --> 00:24:27,216
Listen to your papa.

440
00:24:28,134 --> 00:24:30,636
We'll talk about this later.
Come on. Go to your room.

441
00:24:37,351 --> 00:24:40,021
You will not lay a finger on anyone, Ace.

442
00:24:41,063 --> 00:24:44,108
You're just going to prove
Teo's claims about you.

443
00:24:44,775 --> 00:24:48,279
But can they convince Gem
to speak against Ace?

444
00:24:48,821 --> 00:24:51,574
They can't, right? They're married.
It's against the law!

445
00:24:51,657 --> 00:24:53,784
Unfortunately, there are exceptions,

446
00:24:53,868 --> 00:24:56,829
especially when a spouse
claims to be the victim

447
00:24:56,913 --> 00:24:58,164
of abuse or a crime.

448
00:24:58,915 --> 00:25:01,125
Or if Gem gives consent to testify.

449
00:25:01,209 --> 00:25:02,627
I'm going to block it.

450
00:25:03,211 --> 00:25:05,755
And while Gem is here,
she can't speak out.

451
00:25:06,589 --> 00:25:08,049
Gem is gagged!

452
00:25:08,841 --> 00:25:10,593
But what about Teo?

453
00:25:10,676 --> 00:25:12,220
Can we stop him from talking?

454
00:25:12,303 --> 00:25:15,097
He's already tarnishing our reputation
with the public!

455
00:25:15,181 --> 00:25:17,225
We'll file a defamation case against him.

456
00:25:17,308 --> 00:25:18,559
Slander.

457
00:25:18,643 --> 00:25:22,230
We'll make sure
that he rots in jail this time.

458
00:25:26,609 --> 00:25:28,527
My goodness, Larajean!

459
00:25:28,611 --> 00:25:29,737
What's happening?

460
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:32,365
We just lost some clients!

461
00:25:32,448 --> 00:25:34,075
This is Teo's fault.

462
00:25:34,158 --> 00:25:36,160
Have you talked to Teo about this?

463
00:25:36,786 --> 00:25:38,829
I can't really get a hold of him, ma'am.

464
00:25:38,913 --> 00:25:42,375
I found out about what happened
on the news.

465
00:25:42,458 --> 00:25:46,295
That you're accusing Teo
of having an affair with Ma'am Gem?

466
00:25:46,379 --> 00:25:47,922
But isn't it true?

467
00:25:48,631 --> 00:25:51,008
I don't...

468
00:25:52,468 --> 00:25:54,845
I don't think it's true, ma'am.

469
00:25:54,929 --> 00:25:58,724
Or you just don't want
to open your eyes, Larajean.

470
00:25:58,808 --> 00:26:00,685
You'll keep denying it at first

471
00:26:00,768 --> 00:26:03,271
until you can no longer deny it

472
00:26:03,354 --> 00:26:05,731
and you realize
you're just hurting yourself.

473
00:26:06,857 --> 00:26:08,943
You can't force anyone to love you.

474
00:26:10,111 --> 00:26:11,445
But ma'am...

475
00:26:11,529 --> 00:26:15,616
if you love someone,
you should fight for them, right?

476
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:19,328
Larajean, there are
different kinds of battles.

477
00:26:19,412 --> 00:26:23,040
When you know you love someone
and you won't let them go...

478
00:26:23,874 --> 00:26:25,626
...he can just fool around,

479
00:26:25,918 --> 00:26:28,504
but he will never have
his complete happiness.

480
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:32,758
But in your case,
you have to give up on Teo.

481
00:26:34,552 --> 00:26:38,723
I can never forgive
what he did to my son and my family.

482
00:26:47,523 --> 00:26:50,109
Ma'am, it's time to eat.

483
00:26:51,694 --> 00:26:52,820
Ms. Rica...

484
00:26:59,243 --> 00:27:02,204
...please help me get out of here.

485
00:27:04,081 --> 00:27:07,668
I'm scared for my baby.

486
00:27:11,255 --> 00:27:13,007
Where's Mr. Alonzo?

487
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:17,762
Did they keep him in this house too?

488
00:27:17,845 --> 00:27:18,971
Ma'am...

489
00:27:20,222 --> 00:27:21,390
I'm sorry.

490
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:57,218
Let me out of here!

491
00:27:57,301 --> 00:27:58,719
Gem?

492
00:28:20,408 --> 00:28:21,367
Judge.

493
00:28:22,952 --> 00:28:25,538
Chief,
what can I do for you?

494
00:28:25,621 --> 00:28:26,914
I'm sorry, Judge.

495
00:28:26,997 --> 00:28:30,126
The crime happened somewhere else.
We couldn't control it.

496
00:28:30,209 --> 00:28:31,544
There's nothing we can do.

497
00:28:31,627 --> 00:28:32,461
It's out.

498
00:28:32,545 --> 00:28:34,004
Damn that Teo.

499
00:28:35,214 --> 00:28:38,008
That's a different concern.
It's a search warrant.

500
00:28:38,092 --> 00:28:39,969
We're looking for Alonzo Crisanto.

501
00:28:40,052 --> 00:28:41,887
You should've just called me.

502
00:28:41,971 --> 00:28:43,472
Yes, he's here.

503
00:28:43,556 --> 00:28:45,099
But we're not detaining him.

504
00:28:45,182 --> 00:28:46,600
He's working here.

505
00:28:46,684 --> 00:28:47,977
I'm sorry, Judge.

506
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:50,062

We're just following protocol.

507
00:28:50,146 --> 00:28:52,565
And your name
is getting controversial.

508
00:28:52,648 --> 00:28:56,569
We just don't want
to make this bigger than it is now.

509
00:28:56,652 --> 00:28:57,820
Fine.

510
00:28:57,903 --> 00:29:00,948
But just so you know, Chief,
that Mateo guy,

511
00:29:01,490 --> 00:29:03,159
he was jailed in Morocco.

512
00:29:03,242 --> 00:29:06,120
I'm not sure
if this is a scheme to extort us.

513
00:29:06,203 --> 00:29:09,457
I feel bad for his father.
He doesn't know what to do now.

514
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:12,376
Steven.

515
00:29:12,460 --> 00:29:14,295
Check if Alonzo has finished the job.

516
00:29:14,378 --> 00:29:17,131
- He should get a ride with Chief.
- Yes, Judge.

517
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,610
Alonzo.

518
00:29:38,194 --> 00:29:40,696
Did your son report us to the police?

519
00:29:40,779 --> 00:29:42,823
He could've just picked you up from here.

520
00:29:42,907 --> 00:29:45,493
Why didn't he come home last night, Judge?

521
00:29:46,535 --> 00:29:49,079
I asked him to do some repairs
on the cars.

522
00:29:49,705 --> 00:29:50,789
But it was getting late.

523
00:29:50,873 --> 00:29:52,791
I told him to stay overnight.

524
00:29:54,585 --> 00:29:56,212
But he's done, he can go home.

525
00:29:56,295 --> 00:29:59,131
Is that true, Mr. Crisanto?

526
00:30:03,010 --> 00:30:03,886
Yes, sir.

527
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:10,518
Please tell your son
that we wouldn't lock you up here.

528
00:30:10,601 --> 00:30:12,811
I know the law. That's illegal detention.

529
00:30:13,437 --> 00:30:15,940
And there's no reason
for us to do that, right?

530
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:18,067
Yes, Judge.

531
00:30:21,028 --> 00:30:23,197
Your son is waiting at the police station.

532
00:30:24,323 --> 00:30:25,574
Are you really okay?

533
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:28,369
Would you like to file a complaint?

534
00:30:29,078 --> 00:30:30,120
No, sir.

535
00:30:33,457 --> 00:30:34,458
Go on.

536
00:30:35,167 --> 00:30:36,752
Go with the Chief.

537
00:30:37,711 --> 00:30:38,796
Let's go.

538
00:30:58,107 --> 00:30:59,275
Come in, Pa.

539
00:31:08,367 --> 00:31:09,410
Where are we?

540
00:31:13,455 --> 00:31:14,665
Whose house is this?

541
00:31:15,374 --> 00:31:16,625
Why did you take me here?

542
00:31:18,419 --> 00:31:19,587
Why not bring me home?

543
00:31:21,130 --> 00:31:22,339
Where's Issay?

544
00:31:22,798 --> 00:31:24,967
She's at Larajean's.
I'll pick her up later.

545
00:31:26,135 --> 00:31:27,094
Papa.

546
00:31:27,678 --> 00:31:28,887
How are you?

547
00:31:30,097 --> 00:31:31,265
I'm good.

548
00:31:31,974 --> 00:31:34,059
I'm glad I'm out of that place.

549
00:31:34,143 --> 00:31:36,478
Why didn't you file a complaint?

550
00:31:37,271 --> 00:31:38,272
Come on, Teo.

551
00:31:38,772 --> 00:31:40,524
They're the Veronas!

552
00:31:42,192 --> 00:31:43,652
The father is a judge.

553
00:31:44,028 --> 00:31:45,696
The son is a lawyer.

554
00:31:45,779 --> 00:31:47,573
They're going to destroy us.

555
00:31:48,282 --> 00:31:50,868
If I hadn't reported it,
you wouldn't have gotten out.

556
00:31:51,368 --> 00:31:54,288
The question is,
what are they going to do next?

557
00:31:55,789 --> 00:31:58,667
Especially now that I owe--

558
00:32:00,628 --> 00:32:02,338
We shouldn't anger them.

559
00:32:04,214 --> 00:32:05,299
What did you say, Pa?

560
00:32:06,008 --> 00:32:07,384
I said we shouldn't anger them.

561
00:32:07,468 --> 00:32:09,970
No, before that. What do you owe?

562
00:32:11,764 --> 00:32:13,599
I heard it too, Pa.

563
00:32:13,682 --> 00:32:15,643
Do you owe the Veronas money?

564
00:32:16,268 --> 00:32:17,353
Um...

565
00:32:18,687 --> 00:32:19,938
It's for the estate tax.

566
00:32:22,775 --> 00:32:24,151
It's not true

567
00:32:25,402 --> 00:32:27,237
that I borrowed money from a friend.

568
00:32:28,155 --> 00:32:30,240
I got it from Divino.

569
00:32:30,741 --> 00:32:33,243
I told you I'd take care of it.

570
00:32:33,327 --> 00:32:35,079
Stop blaming me.

571
00:32:35,162 --> 00:32:36,413
We're past that now.

572
00:32:37,414 --> 00:32:38,540
I'm worried...

573
00:32:39,875 --> 00:32:42,378
he might sue me for not paying.

574
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,088
No, Pa.

575
00:32:44,171 --> 00:32:46,215
No matter what happens, we'll pay it back.

576
00:32:46,298 --> 00:32:47,716
With what money?

577
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:48,842
Leave it to me.

578
00:32:48,926 --> 00:32:50,302
I have a plan.

579
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:52,763
But for now, we'll stay here.

580
00:32:54,306 --> 00:32:55,641
By the way,

581
00:32:56,850 --> 00:32:58,644
did you see Gem in the mansion?

582
00:32:58,727 --> 00:32:59,937
No, why?

583
00:33:00,020 --> 00:33:02,231
I just wanted to know how she is.

584
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:23,877
- Let me help you.
- I got it.

585
00:33:23,961 --> 00:33:24,837
Oh, dear.

586
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:27,172
You might be too old for this.

587
00:33:27,256 --> 00:33:28,882
Who's old?

588
00:33:28,966 --> 00:33:31,135
You're just happy now
because you have a boyfriend.

589
00:33:31,218 --> 00:33:33,595
- He's not my boyfriend.
- I don't believe you.

590
00:34:02,458 --> 00:34:05,419
Our shipment can't be delayed.

591
00:34:06,128 --> 00:34:09,798
Otherwise, we'll have issues
with our Myanmar clients.

592
00:34:09,882 --> 00:34:11,216
The timing is bad.

593
00:34:11,300 --> 00:34:14,720
Especially now that
your driver's going off on the media.

594
00:34:14,803 --> 00:34:17,055
That has nothing to do with our business.

595
00:34:18,140 --> 00:34:21,268
Besides, Mateo is a nobody.

596
00:34:21,351 --> 00:34:23,187
How can you reassure us, Divino?

597
00:34:23,562 --> 00:34:25,606
We've been doing this for decades.

598
00:34:25,689 --> 00:34:27,024
And not once

599
00:34:27,524 --> 00:34:31,028
have we been hindered
or ruined by anyone else.

600
00:34:31,111 --> 00:34:32,196
All right.

601
00:34:32,821 --> 00:34:34,031
If you say so.

602
00:34:34,114 --> 00:34:35,657
I will believe you.

603
00:34:35,741 --> 00:34:37,868
But if a problem arises,

604
00:34:37,951 --> 00:34:39,953
you will explain yourself to the board.

605
00:34:40,037 --> 00:34:42,956
We're not going to have any problems.

606
00:34:43,040 --> 00:34:44,583
Are we done here?

607
00:34:44,666 --> 00:34:46,585
I still have something else to do.

608
00:35:01,433 --> 00:35:03,811
Here's the info
you wanted, Judge.

609
00:35:03,894 --> 00:35:05,020
Why just now?

610
00:35:05,646 --> 00:35:07,189
I told you to look that up

611
00:35:07,272 --> 00:35:09,608
on the day I found out
Teo was jailed in Morocco.

612
00:35:09,691 --> 00:35:11,193
Yes, Judge.
It's been with me.

613
00:35:11,276 --> 00:35:14,363
I just filed everything.
I just got back to working on it again...

614
00:35:14,446 --> 00:35:16,615
Excuses are for idiots!

615
00:35:17,533 --> 00:35:18,659
Give me that.

616
00:35:32,130 --> 00:35:34,299
So, they've known each other
for quite some time.

617
00:35:34,383 --> 00:35:35,801
From back in Morocco, it seems.

618
00:35:47,104 --> 00:35:48,313
Yes, Pearl?

619
00:35:49,857 --> 00:35:51,191
What's happening?

620
00:35:51,275 --> 00:35:52,943
<i>I'll take care of it.</i>

621
00:35:53,026 --> 00:35:55,153
The problem, Divino,

622
00:35:55,237 --> 00:35:57,072
is that the recruits
are getting brave now.

623
00:35:57,906 --> 00:35:59,825
They dare demand things from us.

624
00:36:00,909 --> 00:36:03,537
I just can't dispose of them
from lack of replenishment.

625
00:36:03,954 --> 00:36:05,956
<i>There's a decline in the number of people</i>

626
00:36:06,039 --> 00:36:08,292
<i>who are desperate enough to take the jobs.</i>

627
00:36:09,042 --> 00:36:12,379
A bad seed is a bad seed, Pearl.

628
00:36:12,462 --> 00:36:15,966
Don't confuse trash with recyclables.

629
00:36:16,633 --> 00:36:18,635
Otherwise, they're all gonna be trash.

630
00:36:30,314 --> 00:36:32,065
Hurry! Go!

631
00:36:32,566 --> 00:36:33,775
Quick!

632
00:36:33,859 --> 00:36:35,485
You, faster!

633
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:39,406
You, why you didn't follow? Let's go!

634
00:36:57,591 --> 00:36:58,592
Move faster!

635
00:36:58,675 --> 00:36:59,760
Hurry up!

636
00:37:01,178 --> 00:37:02,846
You! Follow me!

637
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:05,223
Go!

638
00:37:05,849 --> 00:37:07,184
All men, follow me!

639
00:37:07,267 --> 00:37:08,352
- This room!
- Go!

640
00:37:09,645 --> 00:37:11,563
Sir... Sir, please.

641
00:37:11,647 --> 00:37:12,814
Have mercy, sir.

642
00:37:12,898 --> 00:37:14,316
Ma'am, ma'am!

643
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:16,151
I'm begging you. Please don't kill me.

644
00:37:16,234 --> 00:37:18,111
My children need me, ma'am!

645
00:37:18,195 --> 00:37:21,531
You dared to steal
and then you tried to escape.

646
00:37:21,615 --> 00:37:23,492
Have mercy on me, ma'am.

647
00:37:23,575 --> 00:37:24,409
What about this?

648
00:37:25,035 --> 00:37:26,995
Are you trying to burn down
the entire building?

649
00:37:27,621 --> 00:37:30,666
Do you want to put
your Filipino coworkers in danger?

650
00:37:30,749 --> 00:37:32,918
Are you going to kill them all
to save yourself?

651
00:37:33,001 --> 00:37:34,628
Ma'am, I don't know anything.

652
00:37:34,711 --> 00:37:36,922
It wasn't me, ma'am. Believe me!

653
00:37:37,005 --> 00:37:38,632
Please have mercy on me, ma'am!

654
00:37:39,007 --> 00:37:40,842
Ma'am, I'm begging you!

655
00:37:42,678 --> 00:37:45,180
I already signed the letter
for your school.

656
00:37:46,848 --> 00:37:49,518
They'll probably understand
why you were absent today, right?

657
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:51,979
Do you think
I can go to school tomorrow?

658
00:37:52,062 --> 00:37:54,106
I'll talk to your teacher.

659
00:37:54,189 --> 00:37:55,899
I'll ask if you can have online classes.

660
00:37:55,983 --> 00:37:57,818
Some schools still do that, right?

661
00:37:57,901 --> 00:38:00,237
But what about my stuff at home?

662
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:01,863
I'll take care of it.

663
00:38:01,947 --> 00:38:04,658
I'll get them and bring them there.

664
00:38:04,741 --> 00:38:06,076
Okay, Teo.

665
00:38:06,618 --> 00:38:09,621
I miss you, Papa, and Ronnie.

666
00:38:10,122 --> 00:38:11,289
We miss you too.

667
00:38:11,999 --> 00:38:15,210
Issay, can you pass the phone to Larajean?
I want to talk to her.

668
00:38:15,627 --> 00:38:16,712
Larajean, here.

669
00:38:18,088 --> 00:38:19,589
Teo wants to talk to you.

670
00:38:19,673 --> 00:38:21,258
<i>Thanks for looking after Issay.</i>

671
00:38:21,341 --> 00:38:22,217
Wow.

672
00:38:22,968 --> 00:38:24,886
Thank you for giving me the honor.

673
00:38:24,970 --> 00:38:26,304
I'm sorry.

674
00:38:26,388 --> 00:38:28,598
I just have a lot
to take care of right now.

675
00:38:29,474 --> 00:38:33,437
Can you bring her tomorrow
to where we're staying right now?

676
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:34,688
Where are you?

677
00:38:35,355 --> 00:38:36,982
I will send you the address.

678
00:38:37,065 --> 00:38:39,651
You haven't explained anything to me yet.

679
00:38:40,277 --> 00:38:42,612
"Frustrated murder of Sir Ace"?

680
00:38:43,196 --> 00:38:45,073
And they're saying
you're Miss Gem's lover.

681
00:38:45,157 --> 00:38:46,283
Is that true or not?

682
00:38:46,366 --> 00:38:49,077
<i>Teo, you're playing a dangerous game.</i>

683
00:38:49,828 --> 00:38:51,663
Well? I'm waiting for your answer.

684
00:38:52,831 --> 00:38:56,126
I think I deserve an explanation
since I'm helping you here.

685
00:38:56,209 --> 00:38:58,754
Don't worry. I'll fetch Issay
from your place tomorrow.

686
00:38:59,588 --> 00:39:00,714
Oh, come on.

687
00:39:00,797 --> 00:39:02,174
Issay is safe here.

688
00:39:02,257 --> 00:39:03,717
I'm just asking.

689
00:39:05,761 --> 00:39:08,764
Okay, fine. I won't push you
if you don't want to answer.

690
00:39:09,765 --> 00:39:13,351
You can let Issay stay with us.
She's safer here.

691
00:39:14,144 --> 00:39:15,979
Okay. Thank you.

692
00:39:22,194 --> 00:39:23,528
Issay.

693
00:39:23,612 --> 00:39:25,280
- Yes?
- Here.

694
00:39:25,906 --> 00:39:27,574
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

695
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:35,916
Of all men in the world, it's still Teo?

696
00:39:35,999 --> 00:39:38,877
You're too loud, Ma. Issay can hear you.

697
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:41,880
So what?
And what are you planning to do with her?

698
00:39:41,963 --> 00:39:45,425
Hold her hostage
until you get Teo's attention?

699
00:39:45,509 --> 00:39:46,760
You're out of your mind.

700
00:39:46,843 --> 00:39:48,762
Ma, can you please not start?

701
00:39:49,221 --> 00:39:52,808
Whatever happens, I won't give up.
I'm sure in the end, it'll be me and Teo.

702
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:55,060
Oh, wow. Really? You won't give up?

703
00:39:55,143 --> 00:39:56,770
No matter what? Hmm? Hmm?

704
00:39:56,853 --> 00:39:58,772
"Teo for the win!"
Is that it?

705
00:39:58,855 --> 00:40:01,149
- Great. Keep fighting, okay?
- Thank you, Ma. Thank you.

706
00:40:01,233 --> 00:40:04,027
Fighting! Just don't come
crying to me after.

707
00:40:04,111 --> 00:40:06,071
This girl is crazy. So crazy.

708
00:40:26,299 --> 00:40:27,384
Pearl.

709
00:40:28,051 --> 00:40:29,719
I heard what you did.

710
00:40:30,679 --> 00:40:31,680
Good job.

711
00:40:31,763 --> 00:40:34,182
Just following your orders.

712
00:40:34,558 --> 00:40:36,852
<i>I have another job for you.</i>

713
00:40:36,935 --> 00:40:39,646
I want you to send me
all the details you can find

714
00:40:39,729 --> 00:40:41,481
on a certain Guillermo Magno...

715
00:40:42,524 --> 00:40:44,609
<i>- and also, a Yana Kassir.</i>

716
00:40:45,819 --> 00:40:46,862
Yana Kassir?

717
00:40:47,821 --> 00:40:48,989
Okay.

718
00:40:49,906 --> 00:40:51,408
I'll send it to you soon.

719
00:41:07,841 --> 00:41:09,509
Thank you for your help.

720
00:41:11,386 --> 00:41:12,929
Here's your luggage, ma'am.

721
00:41:13,430 --> 00:41:15,432
Are you sure
these are all you're going to bring?

722
00:41:16,308 --> 00:41:18,643
Are you ready to see your family again?

723
00:41:21,313 --> 00:41:23,064
Are you going back to the Philippines?

724
00:41:23,773 --> 00:41:25,775
Once all this mess is over...

725
00:41:28,403 --> 00:41:30,071
...this is my home now.

726
00:41:31,948 --> 00:41:34,284
I have nothing to go back to
in the Philippines.

727
00:42:13,740 --> 00:42:15,408
Ma'am? Are you all right?

728
00:42:15,492 --> 00:42:18,870
I don't know, Nanny.
Everything just hurts!

729
00:42:19,412 --> 00:42:22,374
Can you please get me my meds?

730
00:42:23,083 --> 00:42:27,003
And will you let me
light up my candle? Please?

731
00:42:27,087 --> 00:42:28,713
Everything hurts.

732
00:42:28,797 --> 00:42:33,468
But ma'am, we aren't allowed
to give you anything sharp

733
00:42:33,551 --> 00:42:35,720
- or anything flammable.
- Nanny, please!

734
00:42:35,804 --> 00:42:38,265
I need it to calm down.

735
00:42:38,348 --> 00:42:40,600
I feel like I'm having an anxiety attack.

736
00:42:40,684 --> 00:42:42,936
My head is throbbing like hell!

737
00:42:43,728 --> 00:42:44,980
Oh, ma'am...

738
00:42:49,067 --> 00:42:51,444
Nanny, I'm begging you!

739
00:43:33,153 --> 00:43:34,321
Ma'am?

740
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:39,576
Thank you, Nanny. Just put them there.

741
00:43:39,659 --> 00:43:41,411
I'll take them later.

742
00:44:53,733 --> 00:44:55,777
- What is that?
- Judge! Judge!

743
00:44:55,860 --> 00:44:56,986
Ma'am Gem's room is on fire!

744
00:44:57,070 --> 00:44:57,987
There's a fire?

745
00:44:58,071 --> 00:44:59,697
- Oh, my gosh! Raya!
- Sir Ace!

746
00:44:59,781 --> 00:45:01,241
- Ace!
- Raya!

747
00:45:01,324 --> 00:45:02,617
- Raya!
- Sir Ace!

748
00:45:02,700 --> 00:45:04,035
- Gosh, the house!
- Ma'am Raya!

749
00:45:04,119 --> 00:45:05,036
Hurry outside.

750
00:45:05,120 --> 00:45:06,287
Raya, there's a fire!

751
00:45:06,371 --> 00:45:07,622
- Sir Ace!
- Ace!

752
00:45:07,705 --> 00:45:09,124
- Ma!
- Ace!

753
00:45:09,207 --> 00:45:10,667
Hey, what's going on?

754
00:45:10,750 --> 00:45:13,670
- What? What's happening?
- Ma'am Gem's room is on fire!

755
00:45:13,753 --> 00:45:16,798
- Where's Gem? Wait!
- Hurry outside, sir! Go!

756
00:45:16,881 --> 00:45:18,299
- Gem!
- Shut down the breaker!

757
00:45:18,383 --> 00:45:19,300
Hurry, sir!

758
00:46:00,967 --> 00:46:02,427
- Gem!
- Ah!

759
00:46:07,849 --> 00:46:09,434
- Did you see Gem?
- No, sir.

760
00:46:09,517 --> 00:46:10,768
Are you okay?

761
00:46:11,227 --> 00:46:13,438
I need to escape with my baby.

762
00:46:17,734 --> 00:46:18,776
You're pregnant?

763
00:46:23,364 --> 00:46:24,491
Just go.

764
00:46:25,909 --> 00:46:27,035
Just go!

765
00:46:27,118 --> 00:46:29,621
I'm not going to leave you. Come on.

766
00:46:33,082 --> 00:46:34,292
Gem!

767
00:46:34,375 --> 00:46:35,793
Sir, over here!

768
00:46:41,799 --> 00:46:42,884
Gem!

769
00:46:44,552 --> 00:46:46,846
You set the house on fire just to escape?

770
00:46:46,930 --> 00:46:48,515
Are you out of your damn mind?

771
00:46:49,307 --> 00:46:50,600
Take her inside! Hurry!

772
00:46:50,683 --> 00:46:51,935
Yes, sir.

773
00:46:55,188 --> 00:46:56,940
Why don't you just kill me?

774
00:46:59,150 --> 00:47:00,527
Ma'am...

775
00:47:02,862 --> 00:47:05,865
I'm pregnant,
and you're caging me like an animal!

776
00:47:06,407 --> 00:47:09,327
Just kill me instead. You have no mercy.

777
00:47:10,870 --> 00:47:14,457
You don't even care
that you're hurting me and your baby!

778
00:47:14,541 --> 00:47:16,543
My child? Are you sure about that?

779
00:47:17,210 --> 00:47:19,546
Who knows whose baby that is?

780
00:47:19,629 --> 00:47:22,423
It could be Tony's, or Teo's, or anyone's!

781
00:47:22,507 --> 00:47:23,883
This baby is yours!

782
00:47:32,016 --> 00:47:34,018
Get the car.
We'll take her to the hospital.

783
00:47:34,102 --> 00:47:35,186
Yes, sir.

784
00:47:45,029 --> 00:47:46,656
Why do you have bruises?

785
00:47:47,574 --> 00:47:50,285
Ah, Doc... I just got myself hurt.

786
00:47:50,368 --> 00:47:52,120
It was an accident.

787
00:47:52,203 --> 00:47:53,371
But I'm fine.

788
00:47:54,247 --> 00:47:56,791
Doc, our helper left the floor wet.

789
00:47:56,874 --> 00:47:58,001
She slipped.

790
00:47:58,668 --> 00:48:00,461
I'm gonna fire that helper.

791
00:48:02,088 --> 00:48:04,924
It's fine.
I didn't notice the floor was wet.

792
00:48:05,008 --> 00:48:06,426
It's my fault.

793
00:48:08,886 --> 00:48:11,889
What about the bruises on your stomach?

794
00:48:11,973 --> 00:48:13,016
What happened there?

795
00:48:13,099 --> 00:48:15,852
Doc, you know women and their quirks.

796
00:48:15,935 --> 00:48:18,271
Especially when
they're pregnant and very sensitive.

797
00:48:19,188 --> 00:48:20,940
Don't worry about those.

798
00:48:21,024 --> 00:48:24,235
What matters is
she and the baby are fine, right?

799
00:48:27,905 --> 00:48:30,408
Love, you have to be
extra careful next time, okay?

800
00:48:30,491 --> 00:48:32,910
You can't keep getting
into accidents like this.

801
00:48:33,953 --> 00:48:35,413
The baby might get hurt.

802
00:48:35,496 --> 00:48:37,749
According to this chart,

803
00:48:37,832 --> 00:48:41,419
Mrs. Verona has bruises and wounds

804
00:48:41,502 --> 00:48:43,963
just this month
when you took her to the ER.

805
00:48:45,214 --> 00:48:46,799
That was also an accident, Doc.

806
00:48:46,883 --> 00:48:49,927
A few weeks ago,
there was also an accident.

807
00:48:50,803 --> 00:48:52,180
Is there an accident every week?

808
00:48:53,598 --> 00:48:55,433
My wife can be clumsy sometimes, Doc.

809
00:48:55,516 --> 00:48:57,602
Why? Are you insinuating that--

810
00:48:57,685 --> 00:48:59,228
It is a valid question.

811
00:48:59,312 --> 00:49:00,480
There was an accident last week,

812
00:49:00,563 --> 00:49:01,648
and now there's another one.

813
00:49:02,774 --> 00:49:04,525
Also, you probably didn't know
that we were kidnapped

814
00:49:04,609 --> 00:49:06,110
so Gem has a lot of injuries.

815
00:49:06,819 --> 00:49:08,446
You can check that up on social media.

816
00:49:08,529 --> 00:49:10,573
Does that answer your valid question?

817
00:49:12,450 --> 00:49:14,869
Doc, my wife is fine. Our home is fine.

818
00:49:20,375 --> 00:49:22,168
Now, don't meddle in things
that don't concern you...

819
00:49:22,251 --> 00:49:24,128
...if you don't want
to get into an accident.

820
00:49:27,173 --> 00:49:29,258
Now, instead
of asking senseless questions,

821
00:49:29,342 --> 00:49:31,344
why don't you work on
the prenatal paternity test?

822
00:49:31,427 --> 00:49:32,553
Yes, we can...

823
00:49:32,637 --> 00:49:34,514
...if the patient agrees.

824
00:49:36,766 --> 00:49:37,850
Mrs. Verona?

825
00:49:38,810 --> 00:49:39,686
Yes.

826
00:49:40,269 --> 00:49:41,396
The patient is okay with it.

827
00:49:41,813 --> 00:49:43,898
What about you? Is it all right with you?

828
00:49:45,024 --> 00:49:47,777
Now, let's do this.
Because I'm done with your nonsense.

829
00:49:50,029 --> 00:49:51,197
Donna?

830
00:49:51,823 --> 00:49:53,074
Doc, it's ready.

831
00:49:53,533 --> 00:49:54,951
Mrs. Verona, please.

832
00:50:06,629 --> 00:50:09,590
So, we'll take maternal blood
and paternal blood.

833
00:50:09,674 --> 00:50:10,633
From here,

834
00:50:10,717 --> 00:50:14,470
we can run
a noninvasive prenatal paternity test.

835
00:50:14,554 --> 00:50:15,638
Safe for the baby.

836
00:50:15,722 --> 00:50:17,140
When can we get the result?

837
00:50:17,223 --> 00:50:19,350
The standard processing takes a few weeks,

838
00:50:19,434 --> 00:50:21,102
but if you want to get it
as soon as possible,

839
00:50:21,185 --> 00:50:23,271
we can expedite, but it will cost more.

840
00:50:23,354 --> 00:50:24,689
I don't care about the cost.

841
00:50:24,772 --> 00:50:26,065
Do it as quickly as possible.

842
00:50:26,149 --> 00:50:27,900
We'll send these to the lab tonight.

843
00:50:27,984 --> 00:50:29,986
I need answers as soon as possible.

844
00:50:42,248 --> 00:50:43,332
So?

845
00:50:44,709 --> 00:50:46,878
You can't sleep because of what Gem said?

846
00:50:46,961 --> 00:50:48,796
What if I'm the father of the child?

847
00:50:49,464 --> 00:50:50,673
Son,

848
00:50:51,883 --> 00:50:53,593
Gem is married.

849
00:50:53,676 --> 00:50:55,928
But what if the baby's mine?

850
00:50:56,387 --> 00:50:59,056
It won't erase the fact
that we have a child together.

851
00:51:01,559 --> 00:51:02,977
I'm not going to abandon Gem.

852
00:51:03,060 --> 00:51:05,313
If she's carrying my baby,
I'll take responsibility for them.

853
00:51:06,397 --> 00:51:09,734
If it is your child. But what if it's not?

854
00:51:11,152 --> 00:51:12,737
I still need to save Gem.

855
00:51:13,529 --> 00:51:15,198
She and the baby are in danger.

856
00:51:15,907 --> 00:51:17,533
If it's really my grandkid...

857
00:51:18,910 --> 00:51:21,662
I won't be able to treat it
like an animal.

858
00:51:22,705 --> 00:51:23,956
I won't be able to stand it.

859
00:51:24,665 --> 00:51:25,750
Are you saying yes, Pa?

860
00:51:25,833 --> 00:51:26,834
But how?

861
00:51:26,918 --> 00:51:30,755
They have the money,
the power, the connections.

862
00:51:30,838 --> 00:51:32,256
How are we going to go against them?

863
00:51:32,340 --> 00:51:33,841
There's a way.

864
00:51:33,925 --> 00:51:36,344
I've come up with a plan to sneak Gem out.

865
00:52:01,911 --> 00:52:03,830
I thought I was dead.

866
00:52:08,793 --> 00:52:09,836
Not yet.

867
00:52:10,503 --> 00:52:12,171
But you almost died.

868
00:52:12,922 --> 00:52:14,257
The money...

869
00:52:17,218 --> 00:52:18,719
it's at the Centennial.

870
00:53:12,315 --> 00:53:13,441
Where are you taking that?

871
00:53:13,524 --> 00:53:15,151
To the funeral home.

872
00:53:15,234 --> 00:53:16,485
Okay, go ahead.

873
00:53:26,245 --> 00:53:27,079
Teo...

874
00:53:50,937 --> 00:53:52,438
I feel really bad for Gem

875
00:53:53,064 --> 00:53:54,065
because until now,

876
00:53:54,148 --> 00:53:56,567
Ace still has control over
when she can get out.

877
00:53:58,319 --> 00:53:59,987
She's always locked up in her room.

878
00:54:00,071 --> 00:54:01,906
You know, if it were me, Ronnie...

879
00:54:01,989 --> 00:54:04,408
...I swear, I might go crazy.

880
00:54:04,492 --> 00:54:07,370
It's sad to say...
at least now, she's in the hospital.

881
00:54:07,954 --> 00:54:10,373
At least
she's in a different environment now.

882
00:54:10,915 --> 00:54:13,084
I really want to help her, Ronnie.

883
00:54:13,167 --> 00:54:14,168
Why don't you help her, then?

884
00:54:14,251 --> 00:54:15,962
Ace will get mad at me.

885
00:54:16,045 --> 00:54:18,589
Didn't you say
your brother is mistreating Gem?

886
00:54:18,673 --> 00:54:21,717
But I might be breaking
their family apart if I help Gem.

887
00:54:23,135 --> 00:54:24,553
Have you tried talking to them?

888
00:54:24,637 --> 00:54:27,515
Yes. But they didn't listen to me.

889
00:54:27,598 --> 00:54:29,767
And I know if I insist...

890
00:54:29,850 --> 00:54:32,144
...they will make it seem
like I'm the one who's wrong.

891
00:54:32,228 --> 00:54:33,813
I think you've answered your own question.

892
00:54:35,231 --> 00:54:36,565
In your family,

893
00:54:37,775 --> 00:54:39,860
you're the only one
who can do the right thing.

894
00:54:43,656 --> 00:54:45,408
I've talked to Raya, Teo.

895
00:54:46,575 --> 00:54:48,744
She said that she wanted
to help Gem escape.

896
00:54:49,245 --> 00:54:51,664
But... she didn't have the guts to do it.

897
00:54:52,415 --> 00:54:54,166
I convinced her to do the right thing.

898
00:54:55,001 --> 00:54:57,253
She said that she'd do it, but...

899
00:54:57,920 --> 00:54:59,171
she would need help.

900
00:54:59,255 --> 00:55:01,090
And you volunteered?

901
00:55:02,883 --> 00:55:04,635
What if they pin the blame on you?

902
00:55:04,719 --> 00:55:06,470
Raya's not like that, Teo.

903
00:55:06,554 --> 00:55:07,680
Ronnie...

904
00:55:08,389 --> 00:55:10,766
No matter what happens,
she's still a Verona.

905
00:55:10,850 --> 00:55:13,269
So we shouldn't trust her.

906
00:55:13,352 --> 00:55:14,854
Our plan will get ruined.

907
00:55:15,730 --> 00:55:18,441
What if... she reports you to Divino?

908
00:55:18,524 --> 00:55:21,694
Pa, I didn't tell her any plans. Relax.

909
00:55:21,777 --> 00:55:23,320
I didn't mention anything.

910
00:55:23,404 --> 00:55:25,823
She knows that her family is in the wrong.

911
00:55:26,782 --> 00:55:29,535
I just convinced her
to do the right thing. That's it.

912
00:55:30,244 --> 00:55:31,328
Did she say where Gem is?

913
00:55:32,663 --> 00:55:34,874
She said that Gem's in the hospital.

914
00:55:36,167 --> 00:55:38,669
Okay. Find out which hospital it is.

915
00:55:48,429 --> 00:55:49,638
Is Ace coming?

916
00:55:49,722 --> 00:55:50,765
No.

917
00:55:52,141 --> 00:55:53,976
I think we can start.

918
00:55:54,060 --> 00:55:55,728
Sorry...

919
00:55:55,811 --> 00:55:57,730
someone will be joining our meeting.

920
00:55:59,774 --> 00:56:00,691
Excuse me, sir.

921
00:56:00,775 --> 00:56:01,901
She's here.

922
00:56:10,201 --> 00:56:11,368
Hello, everyone.

923
00:56:12,828 --> 00:56:13,996
Before we begin,

924
00:56:14,080 --> 00:56:16,457
given the recent developments
in our family,

925
00:56:16,540 --> 00:56:18,542
I've asked Pearl to step in

926
00:56:18,626 --> 00:56:21,796
to assist in our operations
here in the Philippines.

927
00:56:21,879 --> 00:56:23,714
Now, given our track record,

928
00:56:23,798 --> 00:56:27,176
I've assigned her to oversee
our Myanmar project next month.

929
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:29,428
We need someone who delivers...

930
00:56:29,512 --> 00:56:30,805
consistently.

931
00:56:34,391 --> 00:56:37,812
I'll begin
with the recent status of our shipment.

932
00:56:39,647 --> 00:56:42,399
Despite the issue
involving Daniela and the raid,

933
00:56:42,483 --> 00:56:44,318
the shipment was still successful.

934
00:56:44,902 --> 00:56:47,988
We even exceeded the projected profits.

935
00:56:49,115 --> 00:56:51,283
The entire operation was secured.

936
00:56:52,118 --> 00:56:55,287
We are now positioned
to move forward to the next phase

937
00:56:55,371 --> 00:56:56,747
without disruption.

938
00:57:44,920 --> 00:57:46,005
Teo?

939
00:57:47,631 --> 00:57:49,216
Slowly now.

940
00:57:56,182 --> 00:57:57,433
What are you doing here?

941
00:57:59,977 --> 00:58:01,437
Am I the father?

942
00:58:02,271 --> 00:58:04,190
We're having a paternity test done.

943
00:58:05,941 --> 00:58:07,943
When will the result be released?

944
00:58:08,027 --> 00:58:09,361
I don't know.

945
00:58:11,906 --> 00:58:13,657
But do you know who the father is?

946
00:58:20,956 --> 00:58:22,208
What if it's me?

947
00:58:22,666 --> 00:58:23,918
Then this baby is ours.

948
00:58:25,502 --> 00:58:27,004
But Ace is your husband.

949
00:58:27,087 --> 00:58:29,215
You're the one I love.

950
00:58:35,679 --> 00:58:36,931
We'll run away.

951
00:58:37,890 --> 00:58:39,975
I've got the money Gimo hid.

952
00:58:40,059 --> 00:58:42,311
I've also bought a new car.

953
00:58:42,394 --> 00:58:44,521
We just have to plan when to do it.

954
00:58:50,152 --> 00:58:51,987
What if it's not yours?

955
00:59:06,335 --> 00:59:07,670
Nothing will change.

956
00:59:27,314 --> 00:59:28,649
<i>I remember you.</i>

957
00:59:28,732 --> 00:59:31,026
You were the one
who thanked me for Teo's pardon.

958
00:59:31,110 --> 00:59:32,903
Have you known Mateo for a long time?

959
00:59:33,529 --> 00:59:35,239
<i>Pa, I'm sure</i>
<i>the woman I saw was Mama.</i>

960
00:59:35,322 --> 00:59:37,533
You said yourself that she's already dead.

961
00:59:38,325 --> 00:59:41,203
That baby is not Ace's
but that Teo's!

962
00:59:41,287 --> 00:59:43,831
<i>Whether I'm</i>
<i>the father or not, I will still save her.</i>

963
00:59:43,914 --> 00:59:46,041
<i>I want to help Gem</i>
<i>escape from here.</i>

964
00:59:46,125 --> 00:59:47,584
<i>Ronnie, he's getting crazy.</i>

965
00:59:47,668 --> 00:59:49,920
Something bad might happen
to Gem and the baby.

966
00:59:50,004 --> 00:59:51,130
<i>I'll help Gem escape.</i>

967
00:59:52,256 --> 00:59:53,257
Let's go!
